    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> June 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1781</dateline><salute>Dear
                    Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I have just received your favor; let me beg you would write to <choice>
                        <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></abbr>
                        <expan>your</expan>
                    </choice> servant to call at <persName ref="pe0237">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Pennant</persName>'s in <placeName ref="pl0798">upper Grosvenour street</placeName> for <choice>
                        <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></abbr>
                        <expan>your</expan>
                    </choice> parcel where it will be left next week. There is now an account open
                    between <persName ref="pe0014">M. Griffith</persName> &amp; you: he will fix his price as soon as <del>yo</del>he has done what he is now about for you. What does the
                        the Bookbinder<note type="editorial">The bookbinder has not been identified.</note> charge apiece for letting in our
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0013">Snowdons</title></bibl>.<note type="editorial">A reference to Bull and Pennant's copies of Pennant, <hi rend="italic">The Journey to Snowdon</hi> (1781).</note>
                </p>
                <p>I &amp; <persName ref="pe0014">Moses</persName> beg Miss Bull's<note type="editorial"><persName ref="pe0331">Elizabeth</persName> and <persName ref="pe0336">Catherine Bull</persName>.</note> to favor us
                    with their receit for pasting prints on paper. we bungle dreadfully. my best
                    Compliments attend them</p>
                <closer><salute>Adieu <lb/><choice>
                        <abbr>Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></abbr>
                        <expan>Yours</expan>
                    </choice> most truely</salute> <signed><persName ref="pe0232"><choice>
                                <abbr>T</abbr>
                                <expan>Thomas</expan>
                            </choice> Pennant</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
